<h1>Connections</h1>
<p class="lead">Everything PgKeeper talks to — the databases it dumps, the PITR clusters it
streams WAL from, and the storage destinations it fans out to. Database and cluster probes run
live as this page loads: a bounded <span class="mono">SELECT version()</span> round-trip with
exactly the libpq settings a real run would use. Credentials stay in
<span class="mono">pgkeeper.yml</span> and are never shown here.</p>

<div class="stat-grid">
  <div class="stat <%= @databases.all?(&:ok) ? 'ok' : 'bad' %>">
    <div class="stat-value"><%= @databases.count(&:ok) %><span class="stat-of">/<%= @databases.length %></span></div>
    <div class="stat-label">Databases reachable</div>
  </div>
  <%- unless @clusters.empty? -%>
  <div class="stat <%= @clusters.all?(&:ok) ? 'ok' : 'bad' %>">
    <div class="stat-value"><%= @clusters.count(&:ok) %><span class="stat-of">/<%= @clusters.length %></span></div>
    <div class="stat-label">PITR clusters reachable</div>
  </div>
  <%- end -%>
  <div class="stat <%= @destinations.all?(&:healthy) ? 'ok' : 'bad' %>">
    <div class="stat-value"><%= @destinations.count(&:healthy) %><span class="stat-of">/<%= @destinations.length %></span></div>
    <div class="stat-label">Destinations healthy</div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Databases</h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th></th><th>Name</th><th>Endpoint</th><th>User</th><th>TLS</th><th>Auth</th>
    <th>Status</th><th>Server</th><th>Round trip</th>
  </tr>
  <%- @databases.each do |row| -%>
  <tr>
    <td><%= light_dot(row.light, row.ok ? "Connected" : "Unreachable") %></td>
    <td><strong><%= h(row.name) %></strong></td>
    <td class="mono"><%= h(row.endpoint) %></td>
    <td class="mono"><%= row.username ? h(row.username) : '<span class="muted">libpq default</span>' %></td>
    <td class="mono"><%= row.sslmode ? h(row.sslmode) : '<span class="muted">default</span>' %></td>
    <td class="muted"><%= h(row.auth) %></td>
    <td><%= pill(row.ok ? "connected" : "failed", row.ok ? "ok" : "bad") %></td>
    <td class="<%= row.ok ? '' : 'bad' %>"><%= h(row.ok ? row.server_version : row.error) %></td>
    <td><%= row.latency_ms ? "#{row.latency_ms} ms" : '<span class="muted">-</span>' %></td>
  </tr>
  <%- end -%>
</table>

<%- unless @clusters.empty? -%>
<h2>PITR clusters</h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th></th><th>Name</th><th>Endpoint</th><th>User</th><th>TLS</th><th>Auth</th>
    <th>Status</th><th>Server</th><th>Round trip</th>
  </tr>
  <%- @clusters.each do |row| -%>
  <tr>
    <td><%= light_dot(row.light, row.ok ? "Connected" : "Unreachable") %></td>
    <td><strong><%= h(row.name) %></strong></td>
    <td class="mono"><%= h(row.endpoint) %></td>
    <td class="mono"><%= row.username ? h(row.username) : '<span class="muted">libpq default</span>' %></td>
    <td class="mono"><%= row.sslmode ? h(row.sslmode) : '<span class="muted">default</span>' %></td>
    <td class="muted"><%= h(row.auth) %></td>
    <td><%= pill(row.ok ? "connected" : "failed", row.ok ? "ok" : "bad") %></td>
    <td class="<%= row.ok ? '' : 'bad' %>"><%= h(row.ok ? row.server_version : row.error) %></td>
    <td><%= row.latency_ms ? "#{row.latency_ms} ms" : '<span class="muted">-</span>' %></td>
  </tr>
  <%- end -%>
</table>
<%- end -%>

<h2>Storage destinations</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th></th><th>Destination</th><th>Type</th><th>Backup sets</th><th>Total size</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
  <%- @destinations.each do |dest| -%>
  <tr>
    <td><%= light_dot(dest.healthy ? "green" : "red", dest.healthy ? "Healthy" : "Unhealthy") %></td>
    <td class="mono"><%= h(dest.name) %></td>
    <td><%= h(dest.type) %></td>
    <td><%= dest.set_count %></td>
    <td><%= h(human_size(dest.total_bytes)) %></td>
    <td class="<%= dest.healthy ? 'muted' : 'bad' %>"><%= h(dest.error || "healthy") %></td>
  </tr>
  <%- end -%>
</table>

<p class="muted">Storage health comes from each adapter's own healthcheck — the same probe
<span class="mono">pgkeeper doctor</span> runs. For the full environment check (tools, versions,
config), run <a href="/actions">doctor</a> from the Actions page. Reload this page to probe again.</p>
